reviewText: I was reading a lot of reviews where it said the workouts were too easy. This one was a lot of stretching and muscle toning and the lower body work was a bit challenging.  My muscles are sore today and I worked out almost every day before pregnancy.  I wish that it would move at a faster pace, though...Unlike other videos, the host is not annoying at all and I like her accent.
Title: N/A

reviewText: This by far one of the best Pregnancy DVD's on the market. Tracey is a wonderful, upbeat and very sincere instructor. A true pleasure to workout with and love her accent! I have used this DVD for both pregnancies and I swear this is what helped me recover so quickly!The first section is for your core and [...] with mainly Pilates and some Yoga exercises. The second section is lower body which helped me build strength and keep me strong for my delivery. The Third section was upper body with light weights and the last section which I really loved and so did my husband was the partner stretching. The stretches helped my lower back issues. I am near the end of my second Pregnancy and still have the energy to keep doing the video a few times a week. This is a perfect conditioning workout through your pregnancies!
summary: Amazing DVD Tracey is a true pro

reviewText: I like the video.  It is a great workout for a day you are tired and dont feel like doing too much or are new to excersice (sp).  Since I am not new to excersice, it is a bit slow for me on most days.  I save this for a day when I have had a long day, but feel like I need to get some activity in!  I am only 4 months prego now, so I think this will be better for the last trimester!  Great part about it, it covers the whole body!

reviewText: I didn't realize when I purchased this item that it is a yoga/pilates style workout.  This is fine for days when you're low on energy, but it doesn't really give you a good workout.  I found it to be too easy.  It didn't challenge my muscles the way I expected it to.  Much better prenantal workout DVD's are:  Suzanne Bowen's Long and Lean Prenantal, Summer Sanders Prenantal workout, & The Perfect pregnancy workout with Karyne Steben.
summary: Good Yoga and Pilates, not great for toning.

reviewText: I found this Video very well paced and Tracey cued like a true proffessional. The Video was split in to four sections, CORE, Lower Body, upper body and a section where Dad can join for some assisted stretches which was a nice bonus!This work out was very well modified for different trimesters and great for post natal.I have brought other Pregnancy tapes but this is by far the best due to it's variations of Pilates, Yoga and weight training.I can't wait to do more of Tracey's Tapes....she's very inspirational and charming with her beautiful English accent.

reviewText: Tracey Mallett Fitness Pregnancy System 3 In 1 is a fitness DVD designed especially for pregnant women. The "3-in-1" refers to the combination of Yoga to calm the body and spirit, Pilates to promote flexibility and improve posture, and weight exercises to maintain and improve one's physique. Designed as much to prepare a woman who is expecting pregnancy as it is to help one remain in optimal physical condition throughout 9 months and reclaim one's figure after childbirth, Pregnancy System 3 in 1 applies tested exercises to the upper body, core, and lower body in a routine beneficial to one's whole self. Hosted by international star Tracey Mallett, who applied her years of Pilates and fitness expertise to refining the system, Pregnancy System 3 in 1 is enthusiastically recommended for any pregnant or soon-to-be pregnant woman. 60 minutes, color.
summary: Recommended for any pregnant or soon-to-be pregnant woman

reviewText: This isn't really a workout.  It's like a series of very easy warm-up exercises.  Very slow.  The reason I gave it two stars rather than one is that my 5 year old likes doing the partner exercise routine with me, and it's the only pregnancy dvd she'll consent to do with me; and it's arguably better than nothing.  But it really doesn't get you worked out.  (Also, I personally hate the partner routine; the husband is so smarmy!  But that's a side issue).  This will work for you if you hardly move at all, and need some stretches.  Not for actual working out.
